text: Omg I'm actually crying here- I'm so excited and happy to see that FINALLY Ten will truly have his long-awaited solo debut. I knew from the beginning that he would be one of NCT's first soloists, but seeing it actually happen is still surreal for me. I've always maintained that Chittaphon is one of the greatest idols that kpop has ever had the honor of having. He is simply and LITERALLY one of the most complete idols in kpop, like, there is NOTHING he can't do, and when I say that, I mean it, very seriously, and if you know even a little about his various abilities, you know that "Ace" is the perfect word to describe him. Ten is truly a perfect artist, and I'm so happy, proud and excited to see him finally debut solo. His previous songs are my passions, so I'm so excited about the album. Ten, FIGHTING! author: @fknxrose
text: In NCT Ten's new song, the dream sequence unfolds with him starting alone in an empty car, purchasing just one ticket before a mysterious girl appears. The symbolism points to a solo journey or experience, emphasized by the lone ticket purchase. The girl's sudden presence adds a layer of significance, perhaps representing companionship or a pivotal relationship. The dream takes an intriguing turn in the last scene as the girl disappears, leaving Ten alone in the parking lot. This twist suggests a fleeting or transient nature to the connection or experience, leaving room for interpretation. The dream sequence serves as a compelling narrative device, inviting listeners to explore the symbolic and abstract elements embedded in the story.
